About this item

  • NURSE SHOES FOR WOMEN & MEN - Ditch your old school, heavy, clunky clogs for the super lightweight Anywear SR Angel. These women's clogs provide great cushioning, support, and a comfortable roomy toe box. Ventilation holes on the interior side of each shoe allow airflow inside. These nursing clogs are easy to clean with soap and warm water. Heel height = 1 3/4"
  • SUPER COOL COLORS AND PRINTS - Stand out in a crowd with the SR Angel nursing shoes. Available in a variety of colors and patterns including florals, hearts, patent and metallic colors. New designs added seasonally to update your wardrobe and show your personality. Anywear classic clogs for men and women are great for healthcare workers, chefs, and restaurant staff
  • EXCEPTIONAL CUSHION AND SHOCK ABSORPTION - The Anywear SR Angel work shoes for women and men are made of an injection molded EVA (ethylene-vinyl acetate) upper and midsole for exceptional cushioning and shock absorption. The EVA construction provides comfortable wear, durability, and quick clean-up
  • BREATHABLE REMOVABLE INSOLE - As a medical professional you need footwear that can handle the toughest work conditions and keep your feet comfortable. Anywear SR Angel nurse clogs are made specifically to meet these demands. The insole lining is treated and ventilated to reduce sweat even on long shifts
  • SLIP-RESISTANT OUTSOLE - Anywear SR Angel slip-resistant work shoes for men and women feature a high-traction bottom to add stability during hectic work shifts. The stay-safe outsole on these healthcare shoes makes them a tried-and-true favorite - just what the doctor ordered!

How customer reviews and ratings work

Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

Amazon Customer
4 out of 5 stars
Beautiful shoes, but not for my half-sized feet.
These shoes are absolutely gorgeous, but did not work for me. I wear Size 6-1/2 and ordered up, to a Size 7, based on their recommendation. My feet were swimming around the 7, so I ended up ordering the 6. You can see in the photo, that there is a big jump in sizes. They were too short, and my toes were hitting the tips. They were also a little too tight in the sides. I can see why they said to size up. They are pretty narrow, even for my skinny feet, with low arches. I tried thicker socks with the 7, but still way too long. If I had higher arches, I might be able to get away with the 7’s, but they would’ve been too easy to walk out of them. Not safe in the rain. At least the width was comfortable. I ended up returning them both, since I didn’t think I could wear either for longer than an hour. They also kind of “squeaked” when I walked, but not a deal breaker, because they were sooooo pretty. I feel like they are probably true to size for length, but not width. So very sad.Update: I made the 7’s wearable by sticking in some Dr Scholls arch supports that made my regular shoes too tight. Not perfect, but they do not slip off my feet, anymore. The 6’s are going back, but I’m happy to keep the 7’s.

My feet were swimming around the 7, so I ended up ordering the 6. You can see in the photo, that there is a big jump in sizes. They were too short, and my toes were hitting the tips. They were also a little too tight in the sides. I can see why they said to size up. They are pretty narrow, even for my skinny feet, with low arches. I tried thicker socks with the 7, but still way too long. If I had higher arches, I might be able to get away with the 7’s, but they would’ve been too easy to walk out of them. Not safe in the rain. At least the width was comfortable. I ended up returning them both, since I didn’t think I could wear either for longer than an hour. They also kind of “squeaked” when I walked, but not a deal breaker, because they were sooooo pretty. I feel like they are probably true to size for length, but not width. So very sad.

    Update: I made the 7’s wearable by sticking in some Dr Scholls arch supports that made my regular shoes too tight. Not perfect, but they do not slip off my feet, anymore. The 6’s are going back, but I’m happy to keep the 7’s.
